  :topic: Chapter7/looping_and_counting
  :from_source: T
  :language: cpp
  :caption: Looping and counting

  The active code below counts the number of times the letter ``'a'``
  appears in a string ``fruit``.
  ~~~~
  #include <iostream>
  using namespace std;

  int main() {
      string fruit = "banana";
      int length = fruit.length();
      int count = 0;

      int index = 0;
      while (index < length) {
          if (fruit[index] == 'a') {
              count = count + 1;
          }
          index = index + 1;
      }
      cout << count << endl;
  }
